com.intel.icecp.node.pipeline

Class PipelineImpl<I,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.node.pipeline.PipelineImpl<I,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - Input type
    O - Output type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Pipeline<I,O>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MessageFormattingPipeline

    public class PipelineImpl<I,O>
extends Object
implements Pipeline<I,O>
    Implementation of a generic Pipeline.

    NOTE THAT: A PipelineImpl pipeline may not be invertible. For example, if we have class A and B s.t., B < A, and two operations Op1<Object, B> and Op2<A, ...>, the inverse execution will fail since Op1.inverseOperation() will try to cast an instance of type B into A (throwing a ClassCastException).

      • checkExecutable

        protected void checkExecutable()
                        throws EmptyPipelineException,
                               InvalidPipelineInputTypeException,
                               InvalidPipelineOutputTypeException
        Check whether this pipeline can be executed due to lack of operation or mismatch input/output types
        Throws:
        EmptyPipelineException - if pipeline is empty
        InvalidPipelineInputTypeException - if the input type of the first operation cannot be assigned from the advertised input type of the pipeline, or there are at least two adjacent operations in the pipeline such that the output type of the previous operation cannot be assigned to the input type of the next operation
        InvalidPipelineOutputTypeException - if the output type of the last operation cannot be assigned to the advertised output type of the pipeline

      • checkInvertible

        protected void checkInvertible()
                        throws EmptyPipelineException,
                               InvalidPipelineInputTypeException,
                               InvalidPipelineOutputTypeException
        Check whether this pipeline can be inverted inversely due to lack of operation or mismatch input/output types
        Throws:
        EmptyPipelineException - if the pipeline is empty
        InvalidPipelineInputTypeException - if the output type of the last operation cannot be assigned from the advertised output type of the pipeline, or there are at least two adjacent operations in the pipeline such that the input type of the next (in original order) operation cannot be assigned to the output type of the previous (in original order) operation
        InvalidPipelineOutputTypeException - if the input type of the last operation cannot be assigned to the advertised input type of the pipeline
